snippet.title: The Real Meaning Behind Amber Rose's 2nd Annual SlutWalk
snippet.description:
We took some time to find the meaning behind Amber Rose’s Annual Slut Walk and we found a place that turns and abuse into empowerment and tragedy into magic. 

History: 
In 2011 a police office from Toronto told a group of college women that, “If they didn’t want to get raped, they shouldn’t dress like sluts.” This sparked the birth of SlutWalks all over the world, with grassroots success in over 200 countries.  In support of all the women from around the world that have ever been body shamed or sexually abused Amber Rose decided to found Amber Rose’s SlutWalk, a celebration created to bring awareness to sexual injustices and gender equality.
